benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/customFields - Modify custom fields to bundle

covered: PUT Valid Request scenarios cover typical and edge-case success updates with required and optional headers (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC13, TC14, TC15, TC16, TC17, TC19, TC22, TC23, TC24, TC25).

Error handling and validation coverage: invalid bundleId (TC04), non-existent bundle (TC05), missing header (TC06), malformed JSON (TC07), missing body (TC08), extra/unsupported fields in body (TC09), SQL injection (TC12).
System and integration failures: system unavailable (TC11) and integration data inconsistency (TC20).
Performance and resilience: normal load (TC17), peak load with concurrency (TC18), and recovery from transient network failure (TC21).
Data state variations: no existing fields (TC22), existing fields (TC23), partial updates (TC24), and backward compatibility (TC25).
Security coverage: handling of special characters in values (TC19) and injection attempts (TC12).
gaps: 403 Forbidden scenarios (insufficient permissions) not explicitly tested (only 401).
Caching behavior of responses (ETag/Cache-Control) not tested for PUT.
Explicit race-condition tests for concurrent conflicting updates to same bundle not demonstrated (only bulk concurrency test).
Observability/metrics coverage: no tests asserting logging/metrics exposure for PUT endpoint.
Additional header validation scenarios beyond CreatedBy (e.g., invalid/expired tokens) not covered.
recommendations: Add tests for 403 Forbidden when user lacks permissions.
Add rate-limiting tests to validate throttling behavior under bursts.
Add tests for caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) or confirm absence where applicable.
Add explicit race-condition tests for concurrent conflicting updates to the same bundle.
Add observability tests to verify logging/metrics exposure for PUT operations.
Add tests for invalid/expired tokens and broader header validation.
